&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endoscopy Unit – Mount Vernon Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 hrs per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An opportunity has arisen to appoint two suitably qualified and highly motivated nurses; experience in Endoscopy is desirable however, the successful applicants can expect training, supervision and assessment in practical and clinical skills to gain competencies in diagnostic and therapeutic endoscopy and the assessment of patients prior to, during and after procedures. Once competent you will be expected to work in all areas of the endoscopy unit. You will work within a multidisciplinary team and across clinical boundaries in support of patient care. Good communication is essential, as you will be expected to communicate effectively with patients and other professionals working within the trust. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The service is currently delivered Monday-Friday and provides Endoscopy to inpatients and the occasional inpatient. The post will be demanding but will provide both professional and mental stimulation within a supportive environment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must possess good interpersonal skills and have the ability to be flexible and adapt to the continually changing clinical climate within endoscopy. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jackie Forsyth Unit Manager on 01895279214 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
